<h3 id="how-to-use-const-in-c-on-the-virtues-of-constness"><a href="https://leanpub.com/cppconst/">How to use const in C++: On the virtues of constness</a></h3>

<p><img src="/assets/img/cpp-const-cover.jpg" alt="How to use const in C++ cover" height="66%" width="66%" /></p>

<p>Constness is such an important idea that in certain languages entities are <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">const</code>, in other words, immutable by default. If you want to become a seasoned C++ developer, you must understand how you can use <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">const</code> correctly. In this book, youâ€™ll learn when and how to use it in the different contexts it might appear:</p>

<ul>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">const</code> functions</li>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">const</code> local variables</li>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">const</code> member variables</li>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">const</code> return types</li>
  <li><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">const</code> parameters</li>
</ul>

